{
  "stem": "7093.6",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Rumors were, or we were told-- I don't remember anymore-- that we were going to be taken to Buchenwald, to the main camp, where we would have been exterminated.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we weren't-- then we were three days on the line.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And by the time they got another engine, they couldn't-- they didn't take us to Buchenwald anymore, but they took us to Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in Leipzig they took us to a camp which was called Schonau, which was a very nice camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was already another group of Hungarians there who were very nicely dressed, very well fed, who had a commandant who looked after them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Didn't let them work very hard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Fed them during the whole time and really looked after them and was really wonderful to them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he was now the commandant of this camp for-- for-- we didn't know for how long.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were beautiful showers and we had showers and we had a light meal and we got clean clothes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And which-- And then in the afternoon we were resting on our bunks, on our very clean, beautiful bunks, and suddenly they started-- the Americans started bombarding our camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we laid down our heads.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My hand-- the hand of a friend of mine and she got killed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And quite a few got killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the camp burned down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then they took us through Leipzig, walked us through Leipzig, which was burning because the biggest bombardment was the 7th of-- of April, 1945.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they took us there-- took us to another camp, which was called Thekla.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Now, Thekla was a camp, must have been a very large camp, because there were already lots of men there from Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
